# Git Workflow

## Branch Strategy

```
main -> feature/* or fix/* -> PR -> code review -> squash merge -> delete branch
```

- **Never commit directly to `main`** — always use a branch and PR.
- **Never force-push to `main`** — enforced by `.cursor/hooks/guard-git-commands.js`.
- Branch naming: `feature/short-description`, `fix/short-description`
- Merge method: **squash merge only** — one clean commit on main per PR.

## Agent Workflow

1. Branch from latest `main`: `git fetch origin && git checkout -b feature/my-change origin/main`
2. Commit on branch using `.cursor/skills/writing-commit-message/SKILL.md`
3. Before PR: self-review diff, run tests/lint
4. Create PR via `.cursor/skills/creating-pr/SKILL.md` using `gh pr create`
5. After review approval: squash merge on GitHub

